Flash floods from Ethiopia have have wreaked havoc on farms along River Daua in Mandera County. The floods have destroyed crops, water pumps and washed away nutrient-filled soils in Mandera; which has been experiencing a prolonged drought for the past two years. Speaking during a county drought mitigation steering committee the region’s drought coordinator Hussein Alio said, “We are facing a major drought in the history of this county with vegetation cover index going below average, the animal condition has deteriorated with herders facing an eminent loss of entire stock." The situation in Mandera has gone beyond the severe stage in six of the Mandera sub counties leaving only Banisa wet.  